  intro:
  - text: In the year 2104, humanity stood on the brink of annihilation
    audio: {fileID: 0}
  - text: Humanity's thirst for power led to bio and nuclear wars
    audio: {fileID: 0}
  - text: Risking everything in the line of fire, an organization 'Dreamz' emerged
      to oversee the cleanup process after wars.
    audio: {fileID: 0}
  - text: Trials began to test the abilities of selected individuals to adapt to
      the process.
    audio: {fileID: 0}
  wastageFacts:
  - text: High-level radioactive waste primarily is uranium fuel that has been used
      in a nuclear power reactor
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: e4ce960b0634a4248b96fbee68f88329, type: 3}
  - text: At this time, there is no facility available for permanent disposal of
      high-level waste.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 86b76fe237b914c40883801572683d46, type: 3}
  - text: Most nuclear waste is secured in canisters and buried deep underground
      in sealed tunnels to prevent any waste from escaping.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: bd0cd03d121b7814b942aa98bbcff331, type: 3}
  - text: Liquid and sludge radioactive waste are normally converted into solids
      with cement and glass to stabilise them
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 411cb6f485242aa4699e5d6233b7dd3d, type: 3}
  wastageRevolutionFacts:
  - text: In near-surface disposal of radioactive waste, containers are placed in
      vaults and covered with a membrane and topsoil.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: d1b9ee47b7633174e8d902b3b2611344, type: 3}
  - text: 90% of radioactive waste from nuclear technologies is Low-level waste.
      They are sent for Near-surface disposal.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 16b44c7392200d34e9a93649197036bc, type: 3}
  - text: Intermediate-level and High-level radioactive wastes with long-lived radioisotopes
      are sent for Deep geological disposal.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: ed23b24ce599ad843bb0dd3aa1ee6119, type: 3}
  - text: Deep geological disposal is a multi-barrier disposal involving waste packaging,
      an engineered repository and a geological barrier together.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: a73907e60791775428f22772d7140ba2, type: 3}
  bioWastageFacts:
  - text: Biohazardous waste is any biological waste that contains infectious waste
      like discarded live viruses, pathogens, unsterilized devices etc.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: f8b535312e7a89e46bec32000ba9b3f5, type: 3}
  - text: Biohazardous waste is disposed of by incineration, steam sterilization
      or other disinfection methods.
    audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 4262ac79828458540a10c4c4d93a4cda, type: 3}
